Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithmic approach for random walk on graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the efficiency of the power-of-two-choices paradigm in accelerating the hitting and cover times in various graph classes, which can be seen as an information-theoretic problem. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper studies the behavior of random walks on graphs, which is a common topic in the study of social and information networks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The power-of-two-choices paradigm has been used in the design of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms, so this paper may be relevant to researchers in this subfield. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper discusses the algorithmic question of computing an optimal strategy for random walks, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem.
